node.text:
This. Ya'll this is life lately.  Toys everywhere, a squirmy baby in my arms, a computer on my lap with spreadsheets of numbers, tabs open confirming Q4 and calendars of social media posts open, dishes in the sink, laundry everywhere, dad cooking because I’m boycotting that part of life pretty hard lately….
Working mom life is quite literally one of the hardest things I ever inadvertently signed up for.  Postpartum in my late 30s is different than it was in my early 20's.... in some ways its better because I knew what to expect, and in others it is a million times more defeating because those unexpected times I duck into a bathroom for a quick cry are so sudden and uncontrollable it feels as if I should have more control over it.  What you don’t see here though is the 7 year old red headed boy who came upstairs to play, stole my phone and snapped a photo because “mom, you’ll want to remember how cute you and baby
Eric are.” Sometimes that working mom life is so hard, but those sweet little people we make remind us how very, very sweet life can be.
